Organization Registration and Login
What this feature does
An organization signs up on your platform, verifies their account, and logs in to access their workspace. This is the entry point of the entire system.
Who triggers this
The organization admin. This is the person who owns or manages the business and wants to offer bookings.
Sub-features

Registration
Email verification
Login
Password reset
Session management


SUB-FEATURE 1: Registration
What it does
Collects basic information about the organization and the admin who owns it. Creates two records: one for the organization, one for the admin user.
Fields required
Admin personal details:

First name
Last name
Email address
Password
Confirm password

Organization details:

Organization name
Industry type (salon, clinic, gym, legal, etc.) - dropdown
Phone number
Country

Flow

Admin visits your platform and clicks "Register".
Admin fills out the form above.
Admin clicks "Create Account".
System checks if the email is already registered. If yes, show error "Email already in use".
System validates all fields. Password must be at least 8 characters, one uppercase, one number.
System creates the organization record.
System creates the admin user record and links it to the organization.
System auto-generates a workspace slug from the organization name. Example: "Acme Salon" becomes "acme-salon". This becomes their booking URL later.
System sends a verification email to the admin.
Admin is redirected to a "Check your email" screen.

Data created
Organization record:

ID
Name
Industry
Phone
Country
Slug (unique, URL-safe)
Status (unverified, active, suspended)
Created at

Admin user record:

ID
Organization ID
First name
Last name
Email
Password (hashed)
Role (admin)
Status (unverified)
Created at


SUB-FEATURE 2: Email Verification
What it does
Confirms the admin owns the email address they registered with. The account is not usable until this step is complete.
Flow

Admin receives a verification email with a link.
The link contains a unique token tied to their account. Example: yourbookingapp.com/verify?token=abc123
Admin clicks the link.
System checks if the token is valid and not expired. Token expires in 24 hours.
If valid, system updates the admin status to "verified" and organization status to "active".
Admin is redirected to the login page with a message "Email verified. You can now log in."
If the token is expired, show a "Resend verification email" option.

Edge cases

Admin clicks the link twice. System shows "Already verified. Please log in."
Token does not exist. System shows "Invalid link."
Admin never verifies. Account stays unverified. They cannot log in.


SUB-FEATURE 3: Login
What it does
Authenticates the admin and gives them access to their workspace.
Fields required

Email address
Password

Flow

Admin visits the login page.
Admin enters email and password.
Admin clicks "Log in".
System checks if the email exists. If not, show "Invalid email or password." Do not specify which one is wrong for security.
System checks if the account is verified. If not, show "Please verify your email first." with a resend option.
System checks if the account is suspended. If yes, show "Your account has been suspended. Contact support."
System validates the password against the stored hash.
If all checks pass, system creates a session or issues a token (JWT or session cookie).
Admin is redirected to their workspace dashboard.

Security rules

After 5 failed login attempts, lock the account for 15 minutes.
Show a generic error message. Never tell the admin which field is wrong.
All login attempts are logged with timestamp and IP address.


SUB-FEATURE 4: Password Reset
What it does
Allows the admin to recover access if they forget their password.
Flow

Admin clicks "Forgot password" on the login page.
Admin enters their email address.
System checks if the email exists. Whether it exists or not, show the same message: "If that email is registered, you will receive a reset link." This prevents email enumeration.
If the email exists, system sends a password reset email with a unique token. Token expires in 1 hour.
Admin clicks the link in the email.
System validates the token. If expired or invalid, show an error with an option to request a new one.
Admin enters a new password and confirms it.
System updates the password and invalidates the token.
System invalidates all existing sessions for that account.
Admin is redirected to login with the message "Password updated. Please log in."


SUB-FEATURE 5: Session Management
What it does
Controls how long an admin stays logged in and handles logout.
Rules

Session lasts 7 days if the admin selects "Remember me".
Session lasts until the browser is closed if "Remember me" is not selected.
Admin can log out manually. This destroys the session immediately.
If the session expires, admin is redirected to login with the message "Your session has expired."
One admin account supports multiple active sessions across devices. Example: logged in on laptop and phone at the same time.
When the admin resets their password, all sessions across all devices are invalidated.


What is NOT part of this feature

Social login (Google, Facebook). Not in scope for now.
Two-factor authentication. Add later.
Admin inviting other admins. That is part of Feature 2.